---
---
<section class="relative z-10 w-full max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 animate-fade-up opacity-0 delay-200">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">

    <!-- Left: copy -->
    <div class="relative">
      <div class="absolute -left-8 -top-8 w-32 h-32 bg-rose-500/10 blur-2xl rounded-full pointer-events-none"></div>

      <p class="font-mono text-rose-300 text-xs tracking-widest uppercase mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="w-6 h-px bg-rose-500/50"></span>
        The problem
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-6">
        AI costs scale faster<br/>than your product.
      </h2>

      <p class="text-gray-400 font-light text-base leading-relaxed max-w-md">
        A single provider means paying premium for every request — even the simple ones. Model decisions get hardcoded across your codebase, and flexibility disappears as costs spike.
      </p>

      <p class="text-white font-medium text-base mt-4 max-w-md">
        Most teams overpay because they have no system to choose better options automatically.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Right: visual indicator (consequence) -->
    <div class="relative flex flex-col gap-3 font-mono text-sm">
      {[
        { label: 'Simple summarization task', cost: '$0.024', model: 'GPT-4o', flag: 'Overpaying' },
        { label: 'Short classification request', cost: '$0.018', model: 'GPT-4o', flag: 'Overpaying' },
        { label: 'Complex reasoning chain', cost: '$0.031', model: 'GPT-4o', flag: 'OK' },
      ].map((row) => (
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between border border-white/5 bg-white/2 px-5 py-4 rounded-sm">
          <span class="text-gray-400 text-xs truncate max-w-[180px]">{row.label}</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-gray-500 text-xs">{row.model}</span>
            <span class="text-white text-xs">{row.cost}</span>
            <span class={`text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full font-medium ${row.flag === 'Overpaying' ? 'bg-rose-500/15 text-rose-300' : 'bg-green-500/10 text-green-400'}`}>
              {row.flag}
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-xs mt-2 pl-1">Without intelligent routing, every request costs the maximum.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
